sentences.en: a hitherto unknown species of moth
sentences.cn: 迄今仍属未知种类的蛾

sentences.en: a species of insect previously unknown to science
sentences.cn: 科学上以前尚未了解的一种昆虫

sentences.en: a voyage through unknown territory
sentences.cn: 穿越未知海域的航行

sentences.en: An unknown number of people were killed.
sentences.cn: 丧生人数不详。

sentences.en: For some unknown reason, Mark quit his job and moved to Greece.
sentences.cn: 不知何故，马克辞掉工作移居希腊了。

sentences.en: He is an unknown quantity for his rivals.
sentences.cn: 对于对手们而言，他是个未知数。

sentences.en: He was an unknown writer.
sentences.cn: 他是个名不见经传的作家。

sentences.en: Ignorance of people brings fear, fear of the unknown.
sentences.cn: 人们的无知会带来恐惧，对未知事物的恐惧。

sentences.en: It is not unknown for valuable display items to go, ahem, missing.
sentences.cn: 贵重的展品，呃哼，丢失的话，会众人皆知。

sentences.en: People usually infer an unknown fact from a known fact.
sentences.cn: 人们通常从已知的事实中推断未知的事实.

sentences.en: The authorship of the poem is unknown.
sentences.cn: 这首诗的作者不详。

sentences.en: The best thing to do when entering unknown territory is smile.
sentences.cn: 踏入未知地带最好的对策就是微笑。

sentences.en: The condition is practically unknown outside psychiatry clinics.
sentences.cn: 除了医院的精神病科外，这种病几乎不为人知。

sentences.en: The fate of the three men is unknown.
sentences.cn: 这三个人命运未卜。

sentences.en: The long-term effects of the drug are still an unknown.
sentences.cn: 这种药品的长期作用还是个未知数。

sentences.en: The motive for the killing is unknown.
sentences.cn: 杀人动机不明。

sentences.en: The murderer’s identity remains unknown.
sentences.cn: 杀人凶手身份仍然不明。

sentences.en: the tomb of the Unknown Soldier
sentences.cn: 无名战士墓

sentences.en: Unknown attackers riddled two homes with gunfire.
sentences.cn: 来路不明的袭击者用枪炮将两处住宅打得千疮百孔。

sentences.en: Unknown thieves had forced their way into the apartment.
sentences.cn: 不知名的窃贼破门闯入了公寓。

不知名或不出名的人，未知的事物，<数>未知数，未知数
